# The Odin port is LF-only, regardless of anyone's core.autocrlf. The
# surrounding C++ mirror keeps its own (mostly CRLF) endings — this file is
# scoped to odin_port/ deliberately so it never touches that tree.
#
# Why it matters: stream edits (sed -i, perl -pi) rewrite a whole file with
# LF, so a stray CRLF file turns an 8-line change into an every-line diff
# and hides the real edit.
*.odin text eol=lf
*.md   text eol=lf
